The paper evaluates the performance impact of lambda abstraction in stream processing for a variety of high-level languages and runtime platforms. Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of optimizing libraries, which could also place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The evaluation is based on throughput-benchmarking, which could also suggest the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also deals with query patterns, which could place it in the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different languages and platforms, which could suggest the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
